In order to Back up your domain in Plesk, first login to your Plesk administrative panel as admin and click on domain name you wish to back up, then do the following steps:

1) Click on the icon labeled "Backup" to be taken to the backup files repository.

```diagram

```

2) You can backup locally or remotely. For convenience, you can enter your FTP details and store them for future sessions. To do that, click on FTP Account Properties. On the next page enter your FTP details and then hit the "OK" button.

```diagram

```

3) Go back to the backup files repository and click on the icon labeled "Create Backup". Now, all you have to do is fill in the boxes, give a name to your backup and then click the "Back Up" button. This domain will be fully backed up and ready to store on your PC.
